description:
The product is a commerical carpet tile with EcoSolution Q® face fiber on the StrataWorx® backing system.
EcoSolution Q® face fiber is nylon 6 with 25% post-industrial recycled content. The StrataWorx® backing system
consists of polyolefin compound, recycled materials, and a nonwoven secondary reinforcement layer. The face
fiber is tufted into a primary backing that may contain recycled content, latex is added to hold in the fiber, and the
StrataWorx® backing system is applied.
name: Philadelphia Commercial - StrataWorx® Carpet Tile with EcoSolution Q® Face Fiber

description:
Broadloom Carpet with latex based backing chemistry. Carpet face composition may include either Nylon 6,6 or Nylon
         6 fibers that have been dyed using beck dyeing, space dyeing and/or solution dyeing techniques. Product contains both
         pre-consumer and post-consumer recycled content. Product is manufactured at plants in Dalton, Georgia.

description: The product is a commercial carpet tile with EcoSolution Q100™ face fiber on the EcoWorx® backing system. EcoSolution Q100™ face fiber is nylon 6 with 100% pre-consumer recycled content.  The EcoWorx® backing system consists of polyolefin compound, recycled materials, and a fiberglass reinforcement layer.  The face fiber is tufted into a primary backing that may contain recycled content, latex is added to hold in the fiber, and the EcoWorx® backing system is applied. This declaration covers all products/styles consisting of EcoWorx® tile backing and EcoSolution Q100™ face fiber, with face weights ranging from 12 to 60 oz/sy, and a weighted average face weight of 19.6 oz/sy.   The products fall under CSI 09 68 00 and UNSPSC 3161719 classification codes.
